summary:
The Security Council,
Welcoming the report of the Secretary-General on the UN operation in Cyprus,
Reiterating its call to address the humanitarian issue of missing persons urgently,
Noting the stable security situation but expressing concern over incidents,
Urging both sides to avoid actions increasing tension and work towards a political solution,
Welcoming demining activity and the opening of crossing points,
Expressing concern over construction activity at Ledra Street,
Welcoming the Secretary-General's intention to review UNFICYP's operations,
1. Reaffirms relevant resolutions on Cyprus, particularly resolution 1251 (1999);
2. Extends UNFICYP's mandate until 15 June 2006;
3. Calls on the Turkish Cypriot side and Turkish forces to restore the military status quo in Strovilia;
4. Requests a report on implementation by 1 June 2006;
5. Welcomes efforts to implement the zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse;
6. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
